<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ok i took advantage of a good pick up group in OS to do some tests on Charm. After getting nice and settled into d1 I grabbed a krup knight pet and on the advice of someone on this board gave it 2 weapons (wow it makes a huge difference) turned off all my chat filters and recorded some data. Heres what I found:<P>Level 54 Paladin with AQ<BR>Weapon: Frostreaver<BR>Average dpm: 1357<P>Level 57 Warrior with AQ<BR>Weapons: 2 lammys<BR>average dpm: 1774<P>Level 56 Rogue with AQ<BR>Weapons: Ragebringer, CSS<BR>average dpm: 2778 including backstabs<P>A froglok Krup Knight with AQ<BR>Weapons: 2 Fine steel daggers<BR>Average dpm: 4894<P>It was a little tricky to get the Krups dpm because I had to go in and remove the parts where it was bashing me by hand. <P>The hard numbers here are NOT to be taken literally because there are factors which affect dpm that are unaccounted for. (latency,packet loss, average ping time etc). BUT i think they do give a RELATIVE difference in damage output, even if the numbers may be off somewhat.<P>So what does this mean? Well I have charmed pets many times before but this was the first time I gave the pet weapons. Ive never seen mobs die so fast. After a few kills with my pet ppl started making comments like "Why are these going down so easy?" And within 15 mins the puller began chain pulling while pet basically soloed the mob at camp.<P>Those against charm always ask the question:<BR><B>What about when charm breaks? </B><BR>Well a pet with this kind of devastation capability could seriously rock your world. So even if you are familiar with charm best to refresh exactly what you should be doing.<P>-First and foremost get your buffs up, I am talking full clerics buffs, Shield of the magi, and pally/shaman buffs if they are available and above all Cha buff. That will give you some breathing room. <P>-Next, unless you are a very experienced pet handler get 3 stuns online, I reccomend Flux, Shift, and Slant. These are your fastest stuns and will help you regain control with relative ease.<P>-Lastly use Boltrans if you have it. The fast cast time is a HUGE advantage over allure. Why bother loading lvl 4 mez when you can fit Boltrans so nicely into Shift or Stun?<P>Recharm becomes trivial with a little practice using the above techniques (in combination with your own unique play style).<P><B>Conclusion: Charm is a very very worthwhile skill to master. </B>You can do more damage than 2 or 3 tanks combined. In the above group I almost doubled the rate at which we killed mobs singlehandedly. The added risk involved is something you will have to weigh against the quality of your group. (you see a cleric using celestial heal on you when a mob is beating on you,  think twice about charming)<P>BTW go ahead and forget about using slow if you have a pet, it will save you a slot, and its really not needed with how fast mobs go down.<P>--------------------<P>ZZzz im at work =p
</FONT>
