Viz, I do have to say that you present a really complex mixed bag of stuff to deal with.  On one hand, you seem to jump out and put your "worst foot forward" sometimes, so to speak, but in other instances you always seem to come back and make very informative posts when you've changed your initial impressions.<P>In many cases I've also found a lot of your other posts very interesting and detailed as well.  It's quite irritating when I have to READ all your posts to figure out which camp they're going to fall in today and can't just pin you down to the /ignore list...  Stop DOING that!  <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> <P>I will have to say that even though I don't necessarily cotton to your style and quite often disagree with some of your posts, I do have a tremendous amount of *respect* for the fact that you do take the time to revisit a topic and are willing to admit when you may have been wrong in the past.  Then, to take it the extra step to really analyze something and share it with everyone is certainly a major step above what most people would do.  That raises the "respect level" quite a bit in and of itself.  I wish EVERYONE had the willingness to honestly analyze their own styles as much as that, it is certainly a rare quality.<P>It certainly makes some of those other initially irritating posts (like flaming the clerics on their own turf... /eyeroll) a bit easier to take sometimes.<P>Anyway, just my 2 cp worth.<P>-- Faenyar<P>--------------------<P>Druzzil Ro server
