<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'm just thinking of an idea about refreshing charm that could make the need to deal with charm breaking basically go away. Find approximately the average duration of your charms (or just pick a time), and 15 seconds before it, have someone in your group cast dispell on your pet, (while the pet is guarding as far away from you as the room will allow) and time a mez/stun/charm to land right a split second after the dispell hits. My cleric friend and i used to solo things by him nuking and me timing a mezz to hit so the mob couldn't even move in the time he was awake, i think the same would work for charm. Using this method, a group of a warrior (pull, take a little damage, extra taunting in emergencies), cleric(heal, dispell, buff), and enchanter (you, to charm and haste), could probably be more efficient than a group of 6, as any other members would just suck up exp, as you would have infinite expendable tanks who would break probably a tenth the amount as before. What do you all think?
</FONT>
