Faenyar: *bows respectfully* I really do hope that you and others here wil bear with me thru some of my less graceful posts and enjoy those with value. I will seriously try to get my head out of me arse and quit posting without tact.<P>To the question about getting the krup back under control when its hasted: I try to chain Flux (low casting time) to Shift (long duration) then back away as far as i can before the spells pop up again then turn and fore off a Boltrans. If the Shift gets resisted I cast immobilize (1.8 sec casting time) An back away for recharm. <P>I would recommend using Slant instead of root as your fail safe though until you are *very* comfortable in dealing with a fast pet. Heck if your are even the slightest bit un comfortable get the lvl 4 mez online. <P>The level 4 mez is a true God send when trying to recharm. With experience tho you will find yourself wanting to try to cast Boltrans after shift tho because it keeps the action flowing nicely.<P>--------------------<P>Crush your enemies. See them driven before you. Relish in the lamentations of their women.
