I use charm quite alot myself, and I found that caster generally make the better pets. Now I realize that a knight makes more damage in the long run, but the difference from a wizard isnt that big since both can dualwield just fine. What makes wizards better pets is the fact that they ALWAYS stop to cast some lame spell on you when they break charm, leaving you plenty of time to do whatever you want with the poor thing.<P>That being said, melee pets can be quite cool too, but I wouldnt recomend in situations where it's quite likley that the next pull will be very large.<P>-Aztem
