The inherent dangers of a hasted dual wielding pet is what balances it's incredible power. Learning how to get your pet under control with a certain degree of speed and safety is also a great part of using charm as added damage or crowd control. For the experienced it is a great boon to the group but for the uninitiated it can mean you've just earned some CR time and have 5 new people hating you. As always, I recommend shrinking the pet so everyone can easily tell it is your pet and should be left alone. Paladins and clerics should always be on the lookout for rogue pets and have a stun and heals ready.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
