<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The 50% rule regarding pets and experience is ALWAYS in effect.  With a properly designed group, no single pet should be outdamaging the rest of the group, and thus should never be taking experience.  If your group is very low damage output, and you have a hasted dual-wielding pet that is outdamaging the rest of the group put together, the pet will in fact take half the exp.  This is easy to test with a couple very low-level pet classes alone in a group, with one person using a pet one time, with pet as the only damage dealer, and with both pets up and both pet owners doing damage as well (to ensure that neither pet takes over half the exp).<P>If your group is so low damage output that a hasted dual-wielding pet (anything charmable with Boltran's, not Dictate) is regularly outdamaging the rest of your group combined (i.e. doing more than half the damage), you probably should get a new group.<P>--------------------<P>Waelquin Geistfessler<BR>High Elf Phantasmist of E'ci
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
