<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The message was a long time ago, and it was very vaguely written.  It implied that pets take about 1 or 2% of the exp in a group, but its vagueness was misleading.  On average, over time and over several groups pets take only a couple percent of the exp, because it's very rare that a pet will outdamage the group.  It doesn't mean that pets take a flat 1 or 2% of the exp, but pets take 50% of the exp rarely enough that it works out to 1 or 2% in the long run.  Of course, in a group where you have a charmed hasted dual-wielding pet, that is going to happen a lot more often than the 'average'.<P>It's another one of those situations where independent testing and packet sniffers* show you can't always take what Verant says at face value.<P><BR>* Apparently packet sniffers like ShowEQ show that raw exp values are sent over the wire.  I, of course, wouldn't know this firsthand as Verant says packet sniffers are very bad and they'll ban your account for using one, so I'd never ever use one myself; I just know of people who do.<P>--------------------<P>Waelquin Geistfessler<BR>High Elf Phantasmist of E'ci
</FONT>
