Yes most people use charm because they have found this information out.  There is no greater meat shield than a charmed mob.  That is the biggest reason why enchanters look for undercon'd mobs.  It is great finding that green mob that hits just as hard as a mob several levels higher than it.  The green mob won't break charm as often yet can kill very quickly.<P>I love using charm.  I am always looking for new places to charm solo at.  In groups I'm not sure if I'd risk it because many times if I go down then the group goes down.<P>What I love doing is charming a wurm in BW, buff it with AQ and have it take out the entire giant fort.  I of course stay far enough away that if charm breaks I can make a run for it but many times charm will last long enough for a few kills.<P>--------------------<P>Rashen<BR>54 Enchanter<BR>Vallon Zek
