<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<I>Is it just me, or do you find the longer you keep 1 critter charmed, and the more times you have to re-charm it, the less time charm tends to hold?<BR>Typically, I see my first cast of charm last between 30 and 120 seconds. But after that, it goes down to the point where charm breaks within 1 tick.</I><P>I don't believe this is true from my observations.  I've personally kept a single mob charmed (and recharmed) for over 2 hours, and often keep a single mob charmed through full spawn cycles.  Though I've seen some charms only a few seconds (sometimes even consecutive charms), I still get long charms randomly.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=823" TARGET=_blank>Bick</A> Phantasmist Fennin Ro - Defenders of Ak'Anon
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
